@startuml C3_Register_Shipping_Agents_Logical_View
title C3 – Register Shipping Agents API (Logical View)
left to right direction
hide empty members

skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor White
  BorderColor Black
  FontColor Black
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor Wheat
  BorderColor Black
  FontColor Black
}
skinparam actor {
  BackgroundColor CornflowerBlue
  FontColor White
  BorderColor Black
}

actor "Organization Representative" as Rep

rectangle "Port Logistics Management System (PLMS)" as PLMS {
  rectangle "Shipping Agents Management API\n(ASP.NET Core Web API)" as API
  rectangle "ShippingAgentService\n(Business rules & validation)" as Service
  rectangle "ShippingAgentMapper\n(DTO ↔ Domain)" as Mapper
  rectangle "IShippingAgentRepository\n(Abstraction)" as Repo
  rectangle "PortContext\n(Entity Framework Core)" as Context
}

database "Database System\n(SQL / SQLite)" as DB
rectangle "External IAM Provider\n(OAuth 2.0 / OIDC)" as IAM
rectangle "Notification Services\n(Email / SMS)" as Notif

Rep --> IAM : obtains access token (OAuth 2.0)
Rep --> API : POST /api/ShippingAgents (Bearer JWT)
API --> Service : calls RegisterAsync(dto)
Service --> Mapper : map CreateShippingAgentDTO → ShippingAgent
Service --> Repo : AddAsync / SaveChangesAsync
Repo --> Context : EF Core operations
Context --> DB : persist ShippingAgents and Representatives
API --> Notif : send confirmation (Email/SMS)

@enduml
